                                                  written lines: 25; Uniform layout. Masorah magna often written in the form of figures, animals and patterns; otherwise it occupies three lines in the upper margin and two in the lower margin.Round the margins of folios 2v-7r and 192r-196r there is an unpunctuated text of parts of Psalms in large square charactersRuling with hard point on the hair-side of folios, hardly visible.The beginning of the weekly section is marked by פרש' in the margin. The chapters and subdivisions having been noted by means of Hebrew letters in later writing.
